<m0>HAITI <m1> <ql>
<ue5><m0>Rightist held 8 months <ql>
is freed without trial <ql>
<m1><ue5><ep>
<m0>   <m0>PORT-AU-PRINCE <m0>(--) Rightist political prisoner Carl Denis has been released, eight months after his incarceration on charges of subversion, private Radio Signal F.M. reported Saturday.<ep>
   Police released Denis on Friday from prison in Petionville, a suburb of the capital city, and drove him directly to the international airport where he took a flight to Miami, the report said. <ep>
   Denis was arrested Aug. 18 after giving a press conference where he predicted imminent political turmoil. Police said ammunition and several weapons were found in his home but he was never brought to trial.<ql>
